# Auth Rules

## Stack

- Supabase Auth (JWT Bearer). Profile `role` and `avatar_url` from `profiles` table.
- Middleware: `@src/middleware/auth.ts` — `requireAuth`, `optionalAuth`, `requireRole(...)`.
- Role types and hierarchy: `@src/types/roles.ts` (`isAtLeastRole`).

## JWT TTL (Supabase project settings)

- **Access JWT** lifetime is configured in **Supabase Dashboard** → Authentication → Settings → JWT expiry (not in this repo).
- Supabase default: **3600 s (1 h)**. Verify prod/staging values in the dashboard before changing client behavior.
- **Refresh token** lifetime and rotation: Supabase Dashboard only.
- Client stores `expires_at` in `localStorage` (`arcane_auth_expires`) via `@src/client/services/authService.ts`.

Optional: increase JWT expiry (e.g. **14400 s / 4 h**) for long reading sessions after deploying proactive client refresh.

## Client session lifecycle

- Tokens in `localStorage` (`arcane_auth_token`, `arcane_auth_refresh`, `arcane_user`, `arcane_auth_expires`).
- **Reactive refresh:** `401` on API calls → `POST /api/auth/refresh` (deduped in `@src/client/api/client.ts`).
- **Proactive refresh:** `authService.startSessionKeeper()` in `AppRouter` — checks every 60 s and on `visibilitychange`; refreshes when `< 5 min` to expiry (`ensureFreshSession`, silent — no `AUTH_CHANGED`).
- Silent refresh on token renewal avoids remounting `ReadingMode` / resetting reader theme.

## Reader-safe 401

On reading routes (`/p/*/chapters/*/reading`, `*/reading`):

- **Do not** hard-redirect to `/?login=required`.
- Open `AuthModal` in place via `openAuthModal({ redirect })`; preserve URL for post-login return.
- `ReadingMode` keeps current `readerSettings` / CSS vars on transient auth loss; cleanup `data-reader-*` only on component unmount.

On protected workspace routes (`/projects/*`, `/profile`, `/admin/*`): redirect guests to `/?login=required` as before.

## Roles (low → high)

`guest` < `user` < `author` < `author_plus` < `super_author` < `admin`

- Default for authenticated users without profile role: `user`.
- API project/glossary/export routes typically use `requireRole('author')`.
- Chapter translation review (Critic): `requireRole('author_plus')` — see `@src/shared/featureGates.ts` (`CRITIC_MIN_ROLE`).
- AI smart replace in project search: `requireRole('author_plus')` — `AI_REPLACE_MIN_ROLE` in `@src/shared/featureGates.ts`.
- Admin routes use `requireRole('admin')`.

## Model access (production project settings)

SSOT: `@src/shared/modelAccess.ts` (matrix UI: `@src/shared/accountTiers.ts` → `aiModelChoice`).

| Role | Translate / edit models |
|------|-------------------------|
| `author` | `gpt-4.1-mini` only (server clamp + UI locks premium options) |
| `author_plus`+ | Full prod list (`PROD_TRANSLATE_EDIT_MODELS` in `@src/shared/llmModels.ts`) |

Enforcement: `PUT /api/projects/:id/settings`, `getStageModel` in `@src/services/engine-integration.ts`, job payloads include `userRole`.

## Client gates

- `AuthorGate` — author+ routes under `/projects/*`
- `AdminGate` — `/admin/entities`
- Guests hitting protected paths → redirect `/?login=required`

## Cache

- Auth profile cached in memory + Redis (`CACHE_PREFIX.authProfile`). Invalidate on profile/avatar updates per `@.cursor/rules/cache.mdc`.

## When changing auth

- Update `@src/middleware/auth.ts`, affected routes in `@src/server.ts`, and client gates if paths change.
- Update route map in `@.cursor/rules/routing.mdc` if access levels change.
- Update `@src/client/services/authService.ts` and `@src/client/api/client.ts` if refresh or 401 handling changes.
